			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p144728">Charm bug?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=144728#p144728"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7168">Gharlin</a></strong> &raquo; Dec 15th, '09, 00:48 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Has anyone noticed this bug?<br /><br />I was doing one of the group quests in Brells Rest.  This one involved giving items to gnolls and either leave them alone or defend yourself as they attack.<br /><br />I had a charm pet, a gnoll, which would attack me (and then get engaged by our group's mercenary), if I punted another gnoll.  I would punt the other gnoll so that I could safely give it the &quot;memory chip&quot; item the quest asks you to do since they're indifferent.  The charm pet would stay charmed even though it was going nuts on me and the mercenary.  I didn't try recommanding it the few times it occured.  And I didn't charm that often due to me dying a number of times already.  <br /><br />This strange aggro happened at least twice, before I gave up on charming there.<br /><br />Anyone having similiar problems?</div>

			

		</div>

		
