			<h3 ><a href="#p144736">Re: Charm bug?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=144736#p144736"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2829">lumudan</a></strong> &raquo; Dec 15th, '09, 10:22 </p>

			

			<div class="content">I have had some weird aggro in Brells rest.  I figured it was related to an old charm bug where creatures non-kos to each other but on different factions would continue fighting after charm broke if one was dotted or similar, but not so sure now.<br /><br />This cost us a named once when my pet broke, continued beating on the mob, I BDB the pet, the mob summoned my former pet back... ignoring the paladin that was standing on top of it lol.  Ex-pet went back to pummeling mob and killed it and corpse poofed...;/.  Named was at less than 20% health when charm broke so not sure why it poofed.<br /><br />Have had multiple times where pet would stay engaged on mob after charm broke, and others would then start assisting the pet, I would train more of the original mob over (nestlings) and they would start beating on the pet.... for those who have been around awhile, almost identical to the old pit bug in Plane of Tactics except there is no dot or remaining aggro on the ex-pet that I can see.  Unlike the pit bug, I got no xp and corpses poofed as the mobs died.<br /><br />I wonder if it has to do with some of the coding in that zone for the non-targetable kobolds and gnolls that fight each other.  Have not noticed it in other zones yet, but have spent the most time in BR by far.</div>

			

		</div>

		
